/**
 * Settings Page - Toggle Switch Fixes
 * 
 * ROOT CAUSE FIXED:
 * The main issue was maintaining two separate state systems:
 * 1. Local component state variables (locationEnabled, spatialEnabled, behavioralEnabled)
 * 2. Data stream states from the database (dataStreams[].is_enabled)
 * 
 * These would get out of sync, causing the UI to show incorrect toggle states.
 * 
 * SOLUTION:
 * - Removed all local toggle state variables
 * - Made getToggleState() directly read from dataStreams[].is_enabled
 * - This ensures the UI always reflects the actual database state
 * - The useDataStreams hook already handles state updates automatically
 * 
 * Additional Improvements:
 * - Added loading states for visual feedback during toggle operations
 * - Enhanced error handling and debug logging
 * - Simplified state management by using single source of truth
 */

